.TH TRASH "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
trash \- Send files to trash
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B trash
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,FILE\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B trash
is a script for moving files to trash instead of permanently deleting them. It provides a safer alternative to rm by allowing file recovery.
.PP
The script follows the FreeDesktop.org trash specification when possible.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B trash file.txt
Move file to trash
.TP
.B trash dir1 dir2
Move directories to trash
.TP
.B trash --list
List trashed files
.TP
.B trash --empty
Empty the trash
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/trash/settings.conf
User configuration file for trash preferences
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/Trash/
Standard trash directory
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
